
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `debrelease` baraye sakhtan va montasher kardan package-haye Debian (`.deb`) estefade mishavad. In dastoor asasan baraye enteshar version-haye jadid package-haye Debian be repositories estefade mishavad.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**

    🔹 `debrelease [gozine-ha] <file.changes>` --> 📦 Enteshar yek files changes be archive.
    🔹 `-n` / `--new-version` --> 🆕 Agar version jadid dar archive naboode bashad, ehtmalan etelaati baraye update nadarad.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ debrelease mypackage_1.0-1_amd64.changes

    🔹 Enteshar yek package Debian ba file changes esm-gozari shode.

    $ debrelease -n mypackage_1.0-1_amd64.changes

    🔹 Enteshar package-e jadid ba etela'at kamel agar ghablan vojood nadashte bashad.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ debrelease mypackage_1.2-1_amd64.changes

    🔹 In dastoor package `mypackage_1.2-1_amd64.deb` ra az tarigh file `mypackage_1.2-1_amd64.changes` enteshar midahad, va etela'at enteshar dar repository update mishavad.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `debrelease` command is used for building and releasing Debian packages (`.deb`).  It primarily serves to publish new versions of Debian packages to repositories.

⚙️ **Options:**

    🔹 `debrelease [options] <file.changes>` --> 📦 Release a changes file to the archive.
    🔹 `-n` / `--new-version` --> 🆕 If a new version is not in the archive, it may not have information to update.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ debrelease mypackage_1.0-1_amd64.changes

    🔹 Release a Debian package with the specified changes file.

    $ debrelease -n mypackage_1.0-1_amd64.changes

    🔹 Release a new package completely if it was not already released.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ debrelease mypackage_1.2-1_amd64.changes

    🔹 This command releases the `mypackage_1.2-1_amd64.deb` package through the changes file `mypackage_1.2-1_amd64.changes`, and the release information is updated in the repository.
